<subSubSection id="D1946509FA71D42DFF6E5D28AFFCFA9E" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="7" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph id="99313682FA71D422FF6E5D28AE50FB37" blockId="7.[174,1233,1023,1210]" pageId="7" pageNumber="58">
R e d e s c r i p t i o n. Head (fig. 44, 45). Orbit slightly projected above eye in profile, wide and shining (anterior view); 2 fr s in male, 2 orb s and 2 fr s in female; frorb sta numerous, proclinate, in several rows, elongate; facial bulb large, spherical, 1.1–1.4 
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA71D422FBEC5D17A821FBD7" bold="true" box="[1121,1138,1087,1113]" pageId="7" pageNumber="58">×</emphasis>
as wide as pedicel, slightly flattened; lunule rounded; frons matt, divided into two equal parts with distinct central vertical line; slender vibrissa present in both sexes; maximal height of eye 7.6 
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA71D422FF5C5DB7ACB1FB37" bold="true" box="[209,226,1183,1209]" pageId="7" pageNumber="58">×</emphasis>
maximal height of gena.
</paragraph>
<caption id="CDF1660AFA71D422FF275F99AE89F96C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452834" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452834" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452834/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="58" startId="7.[170,203,1713,1735]" targetBox="[181,1221,1246,1668]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="99313682FA71D422FF275F99AE89F96C" blockId="7.[170,1228,1713,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 44–49. 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA71D422FE975F9AAD9CF949" authority="(Fallen)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[282,463,1713,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinguis">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA71D422FE975F9AAD29F949" box="[282,378,1714,1735]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="58">O. pinguis</emphasis>
(Fallén)
</taxonomicName>
: 44, 45 — male head; 46 — phallus, lateral view; 47 — same, ventral view; 48 — egg guide, left blade; 49 — spermatheca. Scale bar 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="99313682FA71D422FF275FDFA8E5F8A9" blockId="7.[170,1229,1783,1831]" pageId="7" pageNumber="58">
Рис. 44–49. 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA71D422FEAF5FDFAD8BF883" authority="(Fallen)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[290,472,1783,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinguis">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA71D422FEAF5FDFADD0F883" box="[290,387,1783,1805]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="58">O. pinguis</emphasis>
(Fallén)
</taxonomicName>
: 44, 45 — голова самца; 46 — фаллюс, латеральный вид; 47 — то же, вентральный вид; 48 — левая лопасть восьмого стернита; 49 — сперматека. Масштабная линейка 0,1 мм.
</paragraph>
<caption id="CDF1660AFA7ED42DFF2B5B3BAF99FDCD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452836" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452836" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452836/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" startId="8.[166,199,531,553]" targetBox="[168,1218,180,461]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="99313682FA7ED42DFF2B5B3BAF99FDCD" blockId="8.[166,1224,531,579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 50–56. 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA7ED42DFE995B3BADB6FDA7" authority="(Meigen)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[276,485,531,553]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulicaria">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA7ED42DFE995B3BADD7FDA6" box="[276,388,531,552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">O. pulicaria</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
: 50, 51 — male head; 52 — phallus, dorsal view; 53 — same, lateral view; 54 — same, ventral view; 55 — egg guide, left blade; 56 — spermatheca. Scale bar 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7ED42DFF2B5B70AD9DFD2D" blockId="8.[166,1226,600,675]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">
Рис. 50–56. 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA7ED42DFE905B71ADA2FDE0" authority="(Meigen)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[285,497,600,622]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulicaria">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA7ED42DFE905B71ADDCFDE3" box="[285,399,600,622]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">O. pulicaria</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
: 50, 51 — голова самца; 52 — фаллюс, дорсальный вид; 53 — то же, латеральный вид; 54 — то же, вентральный вид; 55 — левая лопасть восьмого стернита; 56 — сперматека. Масштабная линейка 0,1 мм.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7ED42DFF565BFEAEF6FC9E" blockId="8.[166,1225,725,1296]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">
Wing. Costa to M; last section of M 0.85 
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA7ED42DFD3F5BFEAE90FD7E" bold="true" box="[690,707,726,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">×</emphasis>
as long as penultimate; calypter and margin grey, fringe brown. Length of wing 2.2 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7ED42DFF565A3EAF0DFCDE" blockId="8.[166,1225,725,1296]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Mesonotum black or greyish-black, slightly shining (anterior view); 2 dc; ac 3 nearest to sctsctl sut and 10 at level of 2nd dc; halter and legs black.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7ED42DFF565A7EAF0AFC5E" blockId="8.[166,1225,725,1296]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">
Male genitalia (fig. 46, 47). Phallus 0.28 mm long. “Basiphallus elongated, strongly chitinized at base, distiphallus complex asymmetrical” (
<bibRefCitation id="FD1F4B73FA7ED42DFCA45A5EAF81FC1E" author="Spencer, K. A." box="[809,978,885,912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" pagination="773 - 822" refId="ref13519" refString="Spencer, K. A. A revision of the palaearctic species of the genus Ophiomyia Braschnikov (Diptera: Agromyzidae) // Beitr. Entomol. - 1964. - Bd. 14, Hf. 7 - 8. - S. 773 - 822." type="book chapter" year="1964">Spencer, 1964</bibRefCitation>
). Distiphallus as long as basiphallus. Endophallus not reaching basal margin of distiphallus. Proximal part of distiphallus with dorsal bladder, 0.4× as wide as distal part.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7ED42DFF565AFEAF16FBBE" blockId="8.[166,1225,725,1296]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Female terminalia (fig. 48, 49). Both spermathecae equal, rounded, more strongly tapering to base. Proximal and ventral margins of egg guide with sharp, sparse, well-defined teeth. Medial margin with minute dark scales in one row.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA7ED42DFF565D1EAD0DFB3E" blockId="8.[166,1225,725,1296]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Europe (
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7ED42DFD9B5D1EAED8FBDE" box="[534,651,1078,1104]" name="Denmark" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Denmark</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7ED42DFD145D1EAEAAFBDE" box="[665,761,1078,1104]" name="Norway" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Norway</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7ED42DFC855D1EAF36FBDE" box="[776,869,1078,1104]" name="Sweden" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7ED42DFCFE5D1EAF82FBDE" box="[883,977,1078,1104]" name="Finland" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Finland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7ED42DFC525D1EA870FBDE" box="[991,1059,1078,1104]" name="Spain" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7ED42DFBBC5D1EA83BFBDE" box="[1073,1128,1078,1104]" name="Italy" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Italy</collectingCountry>
, former 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7ED42DFF2B5D7EAD7AFBFE" box="[166,297,1110,1136]" name="Serbia" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Yugoslavia</collectingCountry>
, European part of 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA7ED42DFD8B5D7EAE01FBFE" box="[518,594,1110,1136]" name="Russia" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FD1F4B73FA7ED42DFDEF5D7EAF5FFBFE" author="Spencer, K. A. The" box="[610,780,1109,1136]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" refId="ref13567" refString="Spencer, K. A. The Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark - Klampenborg: Scandinavian Sci. Press, 1976. - Part 1. - 304 p." type="book" year="1976">Spencer, 1976</bibRefCitation>
), 
